ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject

Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The next few questions concern your experiences with other people's drinking and drug use. When you were growing up, that is, before you turned 18, did you live with anyone who had a problem with alcohol or drugs?  (By "problem with alcohol or drugs" we mean a problem with alcohol or drugs that lasted at least a month. This could be physical or emotional problems because of drinking or drugs; problems with a spouse, family or friends because of drinking or drugs; problems at work or school because of drinking or drugs; problems with the police because of drinking or drugs (like drunk driving); spending a lot of time drinking, using drugs or being hungover; or a person who received treatment for their drinking or drug use.) ("Drugs" include marijuana or pot, opioid pills or heroin, cocaine, amphetamines or methamphetamines (or meth), and any other recreational or illegal drug.)
Notes: 1 = Yes; 2 = No; 97 = Not sure; 888 = No response

(Mail survey only) Have any of your blood relatives, whether they are living now or not, ever had a problem with alcohol or drugs?

Have any of your blood relatives, whether they are living now or not, ever had a problem with alcohol? (By "problem with alcohol" we mean a problem due to alcohol that lasted at least a month. This includes problems related to alcohol they may have now or that they had in the past. This could be legal or health problems because of drinking; marital, family or social problems (like getting into fights or losing friends) because of drinking; problems at work or school because of drinking; OR a person who received treatment for their drinking.)
Notes: 1 = Yes; 2 = No; 97 = Not sure; 888 = No response
